  schema:name "Linear Logic as Interactive Computation" ;
  schema:description "The Curry-Howard correspondence for linear logic maps proofs to interactive programs — Abramsky showed this in 1993, Hyland-Ong proved game semantics fully models PCF, and Martens built a working interactive fiction language on the result." ;
